30 HOMEBUYERS' ASSISTANCE PROGRAM
31 SECTION 5.1.(a) As used in this section, the following definitions apply:
32 (1) Active duty member. – As defined in G.S. 58-58-335(1).
33 (2) Emergency medical services personnel. – As defined in G.S. 131E-155(7).
34 (3) Firefighter. – As defined in G.S. 58-84-5(3a).
35 (4) First-time homebuyer. – An individual who meets all of the following criteria:
36 a. Is purchasing the subject residential property.
37 b. Will reside in the subject residential property as a principal residence.
38 c. Has had no ownership interest, sole or joint, in a residential property
39 during the three-year period preceding the date of the purchase of the
40 subject residential property.
41 (5) Law enforcement officer. – An individual employed by the State or a local
42 government in this State as a sheriff, deputy sheriff, police officer, or member
43 of the State highway patrol.
44 (6) Public servant. – An active duty member or veteran, or a law enforcement
45 officer, teacher, firefighter, or emergency medical services personnel
46 employed in this State.
47 (7) Teacher. – An individual whose major responsibility is to either teach or
48 directly supervise teaching, as classified by the State Board of Education, in a
49 public school unit, as that term is defined in G.S. 115C-5(7a).
50 (8) Veteran. – As defined in G.S. 122C-465(3).
DRH40426-MC-187 Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 5.1.(b) The Housing Finance Agency (Agency) shall establish a program
2 operating under the Homeownership Assistance Fund, authorized under G.S. 122A-5.7, that
3 provides assistance to first-time homebuyers that are employed full time as public servants in this
4 State. The Agency shall provide, in the form of reimbursement or direct payment, monies to be
5 used for down payment assistance and to offset mortgage insurance premiums charged to
6 program participants. First-time homebuyers shall be limited to the lesser of the sum of
7 twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000) or ten percent (10%) of the purchase price for down
8 payment assistance, mortgage insurance premium assistance, and closing costs. The Agency may
9 provide for mortgage insurance payment assistance at least monthly but for no longer than 60
10 months for any single first-time homebuyer.
11 SECTION 5.1.(c) The Agency is hereby empowered to adopt, modify, or repeal
12 rules and regulations governing the provision of down payment assistance and mortgage
13 insurance assistance provided pursuant to this section.
14 SECTION 5.1.(d) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the
15 Homeownership Assistance Fund, authorized under G.S. 122A-5.7, the sum of one hundred fifty
16 million dollars ($150,000,000) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used for the
17 purposes provided in this act.
18 SECTION 5.1.(e) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025.
